---

### **KEY ARCHITECTURAL DIFFERENCES**

| Aspect | IRC | Nostr |
|--------|-----|-------|
| **Account Model** | Multi-account (per server) | Single/top-level account |
| **Chat Types** | Direct + Group (channels) | Direct only (DMs) |
| **Media Support** | Yes | No (MVP) |
| **Block Streaming** | Supported | Not applicable |
| **Capabilities** | Full protocol support | NIP-04 encrypted DMs |
| **State Management** | Per-account monitor loop | Per-account Nostr bus |
| **Messaging Targets** | Channels (#chan) + nicks | Pubkeys (npub/hex) |
| **Config Scope** | channels.irc.accounts[id] | Top-level channels.nostr |
| **Runtime Extras** | Probing, NickServ, TLS opts | Profile publishing, metrics |

---

### **KEY IMPORT PATHS USED**

All plugins import from:
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` - Core definitions, helpers
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-helpers` - Account utilities
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id` - Account ID normalization
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-resolution` - Account listing/resolution
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input` - Secret handling
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/allow-from` - Allowlist formatting
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-helpers` - Config adapters
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-policy` - Policy enforcement
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-pairing` - Pairing flow
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-send-result` - Outbound result wrapping
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/directory-runtime` - Directory listing
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers` - Status computation
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/extension-shared` - Shared utilities
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store` - Runtime storage

Local exports use `../api.js` or `../runtime-api.js` for type imports.

---

This comprehensive structure shows the OpenClaw plugin system is highly modularized with strong boundaries between plugin-facing SDK and internal implementation details. Each plugin can be developed independently while maintaining consistency through the SDK interfaces.

